Police in Rongo are holding a man for killing his brother over protracted family land dispute. Johnson Ngoje, 34, was allegedly murdered by his brother Charles, over a piece of land belonging to their father. Rongo OCPD Kibet Kirui said the suspect hacked his brother with a machete. "The two brothers have been fighting over a piece of land left behind by their father for some time," the police boss said. He was confirmed dead on arrival at the hospital where he was rushed after the attack. Fanuel Ngoje, a relative, said elders have attempted to intervene on the dispute in vain. The police boss said the suspect tried to escape but was arrested and detained at Kamagambo police station. He urged residents of the area to embrace peaceful ways of resolving domestic conflicts instead of resorting to violence. Click here for the latest political news 